latestIgtvVideos.title: Bhukhi Restoration Project
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A Stream Restoration Project aiming towards sensitizing communities to stop treating rivulets like gutters as they're crucial for flood management. Flash floods are also caused by deteriorating conditions of such watersheds and by reducing anthropogenic stress and reducing unnatural erosion on such water bodies they can be stabilized. They support urban biodiversity which is essential for building a climate resilient city.
Team: @our.common.future

latestPosts.caption:
By @lewispughfdn : Sneha Shahi is a young environmentalist on a mission to protect the rivers of India and the communities that rely on them. Through her work with the Plastic Tide Turners campaign, Sneha mobilised volunteers to help restore the Bhukhi River. Together they collected 700 kgs (and counting) of plastic and solid waste from just 800 metres of river, which led to an increase in sightings of native species in the area. Sneha has fought to increase awareness about freshwater ecosystems and conducted research on the anthropogenic stress to the Bhukhi river due to improper urban planning, bank encroachment and the release of untreated domestic sewage. Her current work involves bringing native biodiversity back to the Tamiraparani River through initiatives which aim to increase environmental awareness among youngsters and provide them with a platform for local stewardship. Stay up to date on Sneha’s progress on her Twitter.

So thrilled to have the work covered on such a wonderful platform and was overjoyed with the choice of picture. I am happiest wading in water! especially with my team members who are the ones that help me make it all happen 🩵
#LoveRivers #phdlife #riverconservation #waterscience #plastictideturner #unep #lewispughfoundation #research #people #work

latestPosts.caption:
Always super excited to drop that rivers, restoration and community participation wala gyaan. Being able to communicate my work to a larger audience (especially so many stakeholders) has been a journey of its own. From dropping science terms to finding more easier terms to get the message across never came to me naturally, but the answer must be in the attempt. I have been tolerated, loved and motivated  by so many people who keep encouraging me each step of the way and I owe it to them, and to the people in the landscapes I get to work with. To be able to explain the reasoning behind river research  and inspire action at any scale possible must be the end goal of  conservation. #rivers #riverresearch #phd #phdlife #tirunelveli #TamiraSES #tamirases  #tamilnadu #nellaineervalam #freshwater
